main event: A luminous object was observed moving rapidly through the sky near Austin, Texas on January 6, 1953.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be traveling between 500-750 mph.
The object was described as being 25-50 feet in diameter and bluish-white in color.
The object was observed for several minutes before disappearing.
The witness was considered a reliable observer.
The report notes that the investigator had no explanation for the observed phenomenon.
